# PRT Score Sheet Generator

Automatically fills out the official **NAVPERS 6110/11 (Rev. 12-2025) Physical Readiness Test (PRT) Score Sheet** using registration data from a CSV file.

The program reads your PFA registration data, groups participants by date and timeslot, sorts them by cardio modality and then alphabetically by last name, and overlays the information directly onto the blank official form. The filled PDF opens automatically for print preview.

This app is designed to take the pfa_registrations.csv test file that is created when you run your PFA sign ups through the pfa_registration app.
---

## What You Need Before Starting

1. **Python 3.8 or newer** — Download from [python.org](https://www.python.org/downloads/) if you don't already have it. During installation on Windows, **check the box that says "Add Python to PATH"**.

2. **The script** — `prt_generator.py` (this program).

3. **The blank PRT Score Sheet** — A PDF copy of the blank NAVPERS 6110/11 form. The script writes data on top of this form, so it must be the same version used to calibrate the layout (Rev. 12-2025). This file is included in the git repository. If you bring your own, make sure to print to PDF first. There will be future updates if the form is changed.

4. **A registration CSV file** — A `.csv` file with participant data. This will be created for you by pfa_registration or see [CSV Format](#csv-format) below for the required columns.

---

## First-Time Setup

Open **Command Prompt** (Windows) or **Terminal** (Mac/Linux) and install the two required Python libraries:

```
pip install pypdf reportlab
```

That's it. You only need to do this once.

If the `pip` command is not found, try `pip3 install pypdf reportlab` or `python -m pip install pypdf reportlab`.

