## CSV Format

## If you used the PFA registration app, all data will be formatted properly. If not follow these directions:

The registration CSV must have the following columns in the header row. Column order does not matter, but the names must match exactly (case-sensitive):

| Column      | Description                          | Example           |
|-------------|--------------------------------------|-------------------|
| LastName    | Participant's last name              | Brown             |
| FirstName   | Participant's first name             | Paul              |
| MI          | Middle initial                       | H                 |
| Sex         | M or F                               | M                 |
| Age         | Age in years                         | 33                |
| Rank        | Pay grade / rate abbreviation        | PO2               |
| Event       | Cardio modality                      | Run               |
| Day         | Day of the week                      | Monday            |
| Date        | Date of the PRT                      | 22MAR26           |
| TimeSlot    | Time window                          | 1000-1100         |

Example CSV:

```
LastName,FirstName,MI,Sex,Age,Rank,Email,Event,Day,Date,TimeSlot
Brown,Paul,H,M,33,PO2,Run,Monday,22MAR26,1000-1100
Jones,Patricia,C,F,32,PO1,Run,Monday,22MAR26,1000-1100
```

