## Basic Usage

Place the script, the blank form PDF, and your CSV file in the same folder (or know the paths to each). Then open a terminal in that folder and run:

```
python prt_generator.py <your_registrations.csv> <blank_form.pdf>
```

For example:

```
python prt_generator.py pfa_registrations.csv PRT_score_sheet.pdf
```

The program will:

1. Read all participants from the CSV.
2. Group them by **Date**, **Day**, and **TimeSlot**.
3. Within each group, sort by **cardio modality** (e.g., all Run participants first, then Swim), then **alphabetically by last name** within each modality.
4. Fill out one score sheet page per group (up to 20 participants per page). If a group has more than 20 people, it automatically creates additional pages.
5. Save the output as `PRT_Score_Sheets_Filled.pdf` in the same folder as the CSV.
6. Open the PDF in your default viewer so you can preview and print (Ctrl+P).

---

## Specifying an Output File

By default the output is saved as `PRT_Score_Sheets_Filled.pdf` next to your CSV. To save it somewhere else or with a different name, use the `-o` flag:

```
python prt_generator.py registrations.csv form.pdf -o "C:\Users\me\Desktop\monday_sheets.pdf"
```

