## Filtering

You can narrow down which participants appear on the generated sheets using any combination of the filter flags below. All filters are **case-insensitive** and accept **multiple values** separated by spaces.

| Flag                      | What it filters         | Example values              |
|---------------------------|-------------------------|-----------------------------|
| `--date`                  | PRT date(s)             | `22MAR26`, `23MAR26`        |
| `--day`                   | Day(s) of the week      | `Monday`, `Tuesday`         |
| `--timeslot`              | Time window(s)          | `0800-0900`, `1000-1100`    |
| `--event` or `--modality` | Cardio modality(ies)    | `Run`, `Swim`, `Bike`       |

### Filter Examples

**Only swimmers:**

```
python prt_generator.py registrations.csv form.pdf --event Swim
```

**Only runners on a specific date:**

```
python prt_generator.py registrations.csv form.pdf --date 22MAR26 --event Run
```

**Tuesday, 0800-0900 timeslot only:**

```
python prt_generator.py registrations.csv form.pdf --day Tuesday --timeslot 0800-0900
```

**Multiple modalities:**

```
python prt_generator.py registrations.csv form.pdf --event Swim Run
```

**Multiple dates and a specific timeslot, saved to a custom file:**

```
python prt_generator.py registrations.csv form.pdf --date 22MAR26 23MAR26 --timeslot 0800-0900 -o early_morning_sheets.pdf
```

If no participants match your filters, the program will tell you and exit without creating a file.

